reviews.title: Plenty of fresh and tasty food make the camper stay in Urk doppet beautiful!lt so beautiful
reviews.text:
Large portions of kibbelings, especially delicious in taste. 
We will gladly come back, recommendation is self-evident. 
Elisabeth and Wolfgang Sibum from D Saterland / Scharrel

reviews.title: Fantastic!
reviews.text:
Very tasty lunch and not expensive!
Don't save eel on my baquette eel.
Also the calzone salmon is fantastic!

reviews.title: Good Food for a Neat Price Friendly People and Super Service
reviews.text:
Delicious food for a neat price received very customer friendly and the Service was fantastic we forgot our cardigan which was sent to us free of charge!
Wonderful place with Friendly People and Super Service!!

reviews.title: Good fish specialties at a fair price.
reviews.text: We had ordered the Étagere with fish.  Good food, nice service, good Price quality ratio. Very professional, recommended.

reviews.title: Fine fish eaten
reviews.text: Delicious fish eaten in a nice restaurant with friendly service. Also don’t have to wait too long but also don’t wait too fast between dishes. In short, highly recommended. PS: given the great quality, think it will be busy during holiday time.

reviews.title: Eating with family
reviews.text:
As a family of 10 children we come to Baarssen for dinner more often, it is always a joy to be there.
With live cooking with an excellent cook, the party is complete.
You will always be very hospitable with very friendly staff.
The food is excellent

reviews.title: Delicious food!
reviews.text: Super quality and very tasty. The portions are fine, on the spacious side. The staff is very friendly and professional. Definitely recommended!

reviews.title: Not good
reviews.text:
The bickering was okay. But the sauce very dirty. Way too much garlic. 
The gourmet was soggy, fat, not enough spices. Bad aftertaste. Too bad.

reviews.title: That's how fish is supposed to be! Blessed!
reviews.text: We were for a short-term holiday near Urk. We decided to eat fish and ended up at Urk at this fish restaurant. It was a simple fish restaurant, but well attended. The fish products were super tasty, fresh and everything looked very tasty on the plates. The service was extremely friendly and correct. The shrimp croquettes and the mackerel fillet were exceptionally tasty. A lovely eatery where I will definitely come back. The prices are also very reasonable. Highly recommended!

reviews.title: It was beautiful.
reviews.text: It was super tasty, really enjoyed, also mega nice and cozy service, I will definitely come back more often, Really doubly worth repeating.

reviews.title: a delicious meal for a good affordable price.
reviews.text:
A delicious fish meal in relaxed atmosphere, friendly service. Good value for money.
In addition, the store is full of a wide selection of delicious fresh fish. We brought a good supply for home in the freezer. 
Friendly and helpful staff, we will definitely be back!

reviews.title: Disgusting.
reviews.text: Ordered 2 portions of kibbeling. Wait 45 minutes. Bickering was mud grease and thick pieces undercooked. Apparently, they don't do herbs. Sauce was gross. Never go there again.

reviews.title: Really a bad restaurant!
reviews.text:
Waiting waiting for someone to come to your table. Finally walked to a member of staff asking if someone can come. There was an annoyed reply that someone like that was coming and she threw a cloth on the counter at the same time. Visibly irritated. There were plenty of staff walking back and forth, but no one to give you a look. You can be busy, but you can also give a friendly nod and indicate that you are busy, but that someone is coming. Other tables were also quite annoyed. 
Eventually a lady at the table, we wanted to eat eel for lunch. But it was already gone. 
You don't think so, noon in a fishing village on the eels. 
Eventually I left and spent my money somewhere else. 
Conclusion: I will never come back here.

reviews.title: Conservative but solid fish preparation
reviews.text: A pretty large and very popular fish shop annex restaurant. On a quiet Monday evening it took some time for the food to arrive. The preparation is conventional Dutch style. Very fresh deep fried fish and also fresh salad. Pretty large helpings.

reviews.title: Eating out in your own village
reviews.text:
Great food during live cooking buffet
Lots of choice, everything was delicious and it was hard to choose 
For less than 40 euros you can eat as much as you want 
We're definitely going to do this more often

tips.body: Reserveer een plekje, anders zit je boven en moet je met de trap of lift steeds naar het buffet

articleContent.title: Your go-to guide for dog-friendly travel

seoInfo.metaDescription: Traveling with your dog has never been easier—or more fun. Cities across the country boast pet-friendly hotels, parks, and activities. With CESAR® brand’s mission to make the world more pet-friendly and Tripadvisor’s top-rated spots, you can plan with confidence. Whether it’s a quick getaway or a bucket-list trip, our guides help you stay, play, and explore with your pup. Grab the leash and go!

articleContent.title: Why Greenville, SC is the perfect mix of adventure and luxury

seoInfo.metaDescription: There are few places that blend luxury and outdoor adventure like Greenville, South Carolina. The days (and mild weather) are made for adrenaline rushes of all types, while the region’s spas, fine dining, and boutique properties serve up luxury experiences that last well into the evening. It’s not hard to dive into a handful of the many treats on offer, and crafting an itinerary that incorporates a little bit of everything is how you’ll find yourself with a Greenville-shaped spot forever in your heart.

I’ve always loved train travel. There’s something special about settling into a window seat and watching the landscape drift past. And as a wheelchair user, that joy only grows when the journey feels easy: level boarding, space to move, and the kind of accessibility that lets you fully relax. For me, the best train rides—like weaving through the Tuscan countryside on Trenitalia—are never just a way to get from A to B; they're part of the adventure.

tripContent.title: Santa Fe: heritage & history on the Original Route 66
tripContent.description: Looking for adventure on the original Route 66? Santa Fe, the oldest state capital, is a must-stop for history buffs. The city, founded in 1610, is older than the United States—but the area has been populated for well over a thousand years. With so much history and heritage, you'll want to allow plenty of time to explore the best of the Southwest—so here are 12 suggestions for things to see, do, and learn.

tripContent.title: Experience Santa Fe: art, flavor & fun on the Original Route 66
tripContent.description: Whether you enjoy nature hikes or margarita trails (or both!), you'll want to embrace everything Santa Fe has to offer. Its unique mix of big-city culture, small-town charm, and Southwestern flavor has earned it the nickname "The City Different." Whatever you're into—from art to opera to world-class restaurants—Santa Fe offers a chance to escape the everyday.

reviews.title: Dirty bickering
reviews.text: Lovelessly made greasy kibbeling without taste. Doesn't look or taste like kibbeling. Major chaos in the store when ordering. We won't be coming back here again.

reviews.title: Small kibbeling with lots of batter and dredging fat
reviews.text:
Ordered a plate with some fries and salad.
The salad was small and more decoration.
The ribbed fries were completely fried.
The kibbeling was downright dirty, small pieces with a lot of batter and mud grease.
There was also no taste to the batter at all.
For a fish restaurant this was very substandard.
The service was also friendly.

reviews.title: A busy place with simple food
reviews.text: We visited at the end of the day and they had ran out of options. They didn't have any of the three meals we tried to order. So we had the regular fish and chips, tasty but a bit too greasy. A great stop though for a quick bite!

reviews.title: Busy place, but that's a good sign
reviews.text: This is the better place to get good kibbeling or Salmon or Lekkerbek, or... Friendly, affordable and good portions. Very fresh and tasty food!

reviews.title: Lovely and Fresh
reviews.text: Beautiful Restaurant with delicious fresh served fish and other meals. You can go for a quick lunch or for a longer stay. Take some fish back home if you want to cook your own dish. I had some stir fried Kibbeling with chips on the side and a little salad and my Aunt had a big salad. It was really delicious. The restaurant has some amazing wall art, it is definitely worth to go for a visit.

reviews.title: Excellent fish shop with attached restaurant
reviews.text:
This a regular stop for me when I’m visiting the area. Usually have lunch there and sometimes take home fresh fish or ready prepared meals as well.

It is located on the harbor and well used by locals – both good signs for a fish shop / restaurant. The menu is quite simple, but the quality is high and good value. I usually have the kibbeling but would not advise to have the special kibbeling which has a sauce added that makes the kibbeling soft rather than crispy. They replaced it with normal kibbeling after we pointed that out.

Service is good and friendly. Very nice décor with murals of local fishing scenes. Definitely try it.

reviews.title: Fresh & tasty
reviews.text: Very good food and yet traditional beautiful dutch sea restaurant with nice working staff, also i liked the interiors of dining area which has some drawings showing the traditional old fishermen

reviews.title: Fish and chips
reviews.text: On a Friday night me and some friends went to Baarssen for some fish. All three of us ordered the "kibbeling" plate. It was served on a big fish-shaped plate and served with some French fries, a salad, a small piece of bread and a little bit of Russian salad with fish. The taste of the food was as expected, the fish a bit greasy but with a nice crispy crust. The salad was fresh. The waitress seemed a little shy but was friendly. Overall, I would recommend this place for a quick and simple dinner/ or a snack in the afternoon.

reviews.title: Service needs a lot more work!!
reviews.text: We're a family of Dutch Australians visiting the Netherlands and travelled to Urk to discover the area. We parked outside Baarssen looking for somewhere to have coffee and lunch. We chose a nice window table for 5 and the brunette waitress who served us seemed nice enough until we asked for 'camomile tea'. No idea what we're asking for (we spoke mainly Dutch but with English also) and returned with a tea chest and said 'this is what we have' and walked off. For 45 minutes after our coffee order came we waited (a) for our coffee dishes to be cleared and (b) for the waitress to take our order. When she was approached (we went to her) that we wanted to order lunch (at this stage the cafe was starting to get busy), she said that she would get to us when she was ready. She continued to ignore our table but took orders from tables around us. We've never experienced such BAD service in a cafe before. Coffee and Apple Gebak that we had was nice but was marred by this waitresses lack of professionalism. We do NOT intend on visiting this place again. Unimpressed!!😡

reviews.title: Great range and affordable
reviews.text:
We stopped here unplanned when passing through Urk. We had some fish and chips which was decent serving size and great taste. The place looks very tidy and clean and has a great selection of fish and other seafood. Also there is plenty for the non seafood eaters.

Plenty of parking close

reviews.title: Great fish dishes right in the harbor
reviews.text: We frequently make a visit to Baarssen on Urk. Yes, on Urk, remember, it used to be an island, before they used windmills to pump all the water out and dried out the "Noordoostpolder". Baarssen is a great place to visit with the family and taste some of the local fish dishes. Lots of choice. Enjoy!

reviews.title: Delicious fish buffet
reviews.text: Excellent quality fish,  after eating here you won't want fish anywhere else.  It's extremely fresh,  and delicious. We ate the all you can eat buffet.  I suggest you come hungry,  because there are fish salads,  soup, bread, hot fish dishes (including kibbeling), and fish made to order on the griddle.  Of I ever have reason to be in Urk again, I will definitely visit there.

reviews.title: Herring at its best
reviews.text: This is essentially a great fish shop with a small cafe area for meals. Looks like it does a big trade with tourists and campers who pack the harbor town centre. Was in Urk a couple of times this trip and each time enjoyed watching my fresh salted raw herring being prepared by an expert. Add chopped onions, tip your head back, bite and within seconds you are Dutch! Outdoor and indoor seating for snackers and a small dining room for lunch and dinner (only early evening).

reviews.title: Fish, fish, fish
reviews.text: A nice place to eat a local dish. A takeaway place, but also a good spot to eat at a table. Not fancy, but a good quality for fish. They have a wide variouty. Fresh and well flavoured. Even a local couple in traditional dresh was having a lunch here. Just near the harbour.

reviews.title: Fresh fish and nice staff
reviews.text: Every time I come to Urk for business, I have my meal in the Baarssen restaurant. It is a local restaurant with fresh fish and lots of choices. The staff is very efficient, friendly and gives you nice daily menu suggestions. Excellent value for money.

reviews.title: Baarssen: A Great Fish restaurant at Urk
reviews.text:
Urk was an island before the “afsluitdijk” (Enclosure Dam) an island. Many people from the island used to live from the fishery.
Today Urk is on a half island. It is easier to reach the mainland. Anyway many people live from fishery there.
When we arrived at the center of Urk, we saw a fish selling shop and just beside a trendy fish restaurant. The decoration of the restaurant is great. Paintings from “old Urk” etc. The fish you can eat there is among the very best we ever ate.
This restaurant is worth an excursion.
pore
